## Uber Eats Order Tracker

Displays live Uber Eats order status — restaurant name, order phase, 5-step
progress bar, ETA badge, and a map showing the courier, restaurant, and
delivery address.  When an order is detected for the first time, PiHome
navigates to this screen and plays a notification chime.

### Why it uses session cookies

Uber Eats has no official consumer-facing API.  The screen accesses the same
internal `getActiveOrdersV1` endpoint that ubereats.com uses in your browser,
which is authenticated with your browser session cookies.

### Setup

1. Open https://www.ubereats.com in a desktop browser and log in.
2. Open DevTools (F12) → Network tab.
3. Either place an active order or refresh the page while one is in progress.
4. In the Network tab, look for a request named **getActiveOrdersV1**.
5. Click it → Request Headers panel.
6. Copy the full value of the **cookie** header (it will be a long string).
7. Copy the value of the **x-csrf-token** header.
8. In PiHome → Settings → Uber Eats, paste both values into the respective fields.

PiHome will immediately start polling and will display any active orders.

### Token expiry

Browser session cookies expire over time (typically days to weeks).  When the
screen stops showing your orders, repeat the steps above to grab fresh values.
No restart of PiHome is required — pasting new values in Settings takes effect
immediately.

### Polling schedule

By default the screen polls every 60 seconds between 5 PM and 11 PM.  It also
polls immediately whenever you navigate to the screen.  The hours can be
adjusted in Settings (24-hour format).
